<br>
“My game, my rules,” he reminded her. Chloe’s mouth dropped open for a moment, but she quickly closed it and got a determined look on her face.<br>
<br>
“Okay,” she agreed. “I can’t believe I’m agreeing to this,” she mumbled. “What are the rules?” Lex smirked.<br>
<br>
“You know the first one,” he said with a smirk. Chloe rolled her eyes. “Second, you have to tell Pete, but only Pete. Despite what people might think, I don’t have a death wish. But it will ruin the game if everyone but Clark is in on it.” Chloe nodded. ‘That sounds reasonable,’ she thought. “And third, you have to be seen in public with me, even if Clark isn’t around.” Chloe snorted.<br>
<br>
“I’m in public with you right now and Clark is nowhere to be seen,” she pointed out. Lex got a glint in his eye.<br>
<br>
“I was thinking along the lines of something more substantial than coffee,” he said. Chloe frowned. “Do we have a game?” Lex asked and stuck out his hand. Chloe looked thoughtful, but Lex was counting on her stubborn streak winning out.<br>
<br>
“I don’t know,” she said. “I mean, how will Pete play?” Lex frowned. He hadn’t thought about that.<br>
<br>
“You’re going to tell him so he can play along, act as if your act is legitimate,” he said with a confidence that sounded like he had planned it all along. Chloe laughed again.<br>
<br>
“I don’t know if he’ll go for it Lex, he doesn’t like you very much,” Chloe observed. Lex smiled.<br>
<br>
“He doesn’t like me at all,” Lex replied. Chloe arched an eyebrow.<br>
<br>
“So why are you smiling?” She asked. His smile turned into a smirk.<br>
<br>
“You called me by my first name,” he said. Chloe narrowed her eyes playfully at him.<br>
<br>
“No,” she argued. “I called you by your nickname. As I remember, Alexander is your first name.”<br>
<br>
“Semantics,” he said. “So, now that you know Pete’s role, do we have a game?” Chloe shook her head and smiled.<br>
<br>
“A game has to have a way to win,” she said. “How do you determine the winner?”<br>
<br>
“Some games are played merely for sport Chloe,” Lex answered. She smiled when he emphasized her first name.<br>
<br>
“Well I’m not going to play if I don’t get a chance at winning,” she responded. Lex chuckled.<br>
<br>
“Spoken like a true competitor,” he said. Lex paused and looked thoughtful. “The first one to tell any person about the game loses.”<br>
<br>
“That still leaves two potential winners,” Chloe said. Lex shrugged and took a sip of his coffee.<br>
<br>
“So the one loser will buy the two winners dinner,” he said.<br>
<br>
“Coffee,” she argued. “Little cash flow problem on my side, remember?”<br>
<br>
“You’re presuming that you’ll lose. I wouldn’t have thought that about you,” he said with a smirk.<br>
<br>
“No,” she said. “I’m presuming Pete will lose, and he’s in the same financial bracket I am.” Lex nodded.<br>
<br>
“Alright. Coffee it is,” he agreed. Chloe smiled and noticed Clark coming into the Talon.<br>
<br>
“We have a game,” she said. Lex grinned.<br>
<br>
“I take it that Clark just entered the building,” he said.<br>
<br>
“Funny, I didn’t notice eyes in the back of your head,” Chloe retorted. Lex shrugged.<br>
<br>
“The look on your face was enough,” he replied, not letting the twinge of sadness he felt creep into his voice.<br>
<br>
“You’re so going to lose,” she said to Lex with a smile and waved to Clark. “You think you can handle this?” Lex raised an eyebrow at the evil grin that crept across her lips. Clark came over and sat down in the chair directly across from them.<br>
<br>
“Hey guys,” Clark greeted. He looked back and forth between them, noting the looks on their faces with suspicion. “Please tell me you guys aren’t going to play Lana zone.” Chloe ripped her eye contact away from Lex and smiled broadly at Clark.<br>
<br>
“Of course not,” she said. “Lex and I have found better things to do with our time.” Lex had to hold back a chuckle at Clark’s confused, yet still suspicious look.<br>
<br>
“Substantially better,” Lex agreed and winked at Chloe. The action didn’t escape Clark’s attention and he tilted his head at them.<br>
<br>
“What are you two up to?” Clark asked. Chloe gave Lex another evil grin and then she slid her hand onto his thigh. He grinned back at her. Little did she know she was going right along with his real plan. Unfortunately, Clark didn’t notice where Chloe placed her hand.<br>
<br>
“Chloe and I were just discussing our upcoming trip to Metropolis Clark,” Lex answered. Clark raised his eyebrows in surprise and looked at Chloe.<br>
<br>
“You’re going to Metropolis with Lex?” He asked in disbelief. Chloe kept her attention focused on Lex. That was the game right? She gazed at him like he had just stepped out of one of her dreams and then she smiled.<br>
<br>
“Uh huh,” she answered. Clark furrowed his brow. Lex glanced over at Chloe and couldn’t stop a grin of delight from covering his mouth. ‘Okay, now I know something’s up,’ Clark thought to himself. He was brought out of his thoughts when he saw Lana come in. Chloe noticed too and she smiled at Clark. “Are you sure we can’t play Lana zone?” She teased. Clark gave her a half smile.<br>
<br>
“Yes, I’m sure,” he said as he rose from his seat. “Be right back you guys.” Lex took Clark’s momentary absence as an opportunity. He leaned over and whispered into Chloe’s ear.<br>
<br>
“You’re entirely too good at this,” he said. “I may have underestimated my competition.” Chloe smiled in agreement. Clark started talking to Lana and Lana glanced over in time to catch Lex’s mouth next to Chloe’s ear. Her mouth dropped open a little.<br>
<br>
“Um, Clark?” She asked.<br>
<br>
“Yeah?” He replied with a shy smile. She tilted her head and furrowed her brow.<br>
<br>
“When did Chloe and Lex start dating?” Lana asked. Clark gave her a bemused expression.<br>
<br>
“What do you mean?” He asked. She motioned toward the couple and Clark followed her gaze with his eyes. Lex had gone back to his upright position in his chair by the time Clark looked over though, and Clark just saw them talking. “Oh, they’re just talking about going to Metropolis,” he said as if it were nothing. Lana looked at him in shock, but quickly shook it off.<br>
<br>
“Okay,” she said, hoping that her tone didn’t give away her suspicions. Chloe sighed when she saw Clark talking to Lana.<br>
<br>
“He doesn’t have to be paying attention,” Lex reminded her. Chloe nodded and took a drink from her cup.<br>
<br>
“I know,” she said. “But,” Chloe paused when she saw a woman come in through the front door. “Isn’t that?” She motioned to the woman with her head. Lex turned his head and frowned.<br>
<br>
“Victoria,” he answered. Lex scowled and Chloe grinned almost giddily. Lex raised a questioning eyebrow at her.<br>
<br>
“I’m going to win,” she taunted. Lex grinned at Chloe as Victoria walked over to them.<br>
<br>
“Don’t count on it,” he responded. Lex looked up at Victoria when she arrived at their table, but he made no effort to stand.<br>
<br>
“Lex,” Victoria cooed.<br>
<br>
“Victoria,” Lex said dryly and took a sip of his coffee. Victoria noticed Chloe’s hand was on Lex’s thigh and she narrowed her eyes at her. Chloe just smiled. ‘I’m going to win,’ Chloe thought smugly. Chloe rose from her seat and motioned to Lex’s cup.<br>
<br>
“I need a refill,” she stated. “You want one too?” Lex gave her a half smile and nodded once. Chloe decided to take him by surprise, and leaned over and kissed him. Lex quickly took advantage of the situation and pulled her onto his lap, where he deepened the kiss. Victoria crossed her arms and seethed. Chloe pulled away from the kiss and tried to hide her shock at what had just happened.<br>
<br>
“I’m sorry Victoria, have you met my girlfriend?” Lex asked with an amused expression. Lana and Clark had been on their way to the table when they saw the kiss and heard what Lex said. Lana turned to Clark.<br>
<br>
“I told you so,” she said.<br>
