<br>
“Chloe,” she said as an introduction. Victoria glared at her, but she shook her hand.<br>
<br>
“Victoria,” she announced. Chloe nodded and pulled back her hand, only to place it on Lex’s chest. Pete walked into the Talon just in time to see the hand shake and was wondering just what the hell was going on. He smiled when he saw Clark and Lana openly gaping at Chloe and Lex though, and figured that they must be playing Lana zone or a different game. He walked over and stood next to Clark.<br>
<br>
“So Chloe’s meeting the ex huh? Weird,” Pete commented. Clark and Lana both looked at him with almost horrified expressions on their faces. Pete tried to keep himself from laughing. “Don’t worry, she can handle herself.”<br>
<br>
“So what brings you to Smallville Victoria?” Chloe asked in a sickeningly sweet voice. She was going to be damned if she let this pompous bitch intimidate her. Victoria narrowed her eyes at her.<br>
<br>
“Lionel, Lex’s father,” Victoria answered. Chloe smiled.<br>
<br>
“I’m aware of who Lionel is, thanks,” she said sarcastically. Chloe glanced over at her friends when she heard Pete’s snicker. She shot him a silent look that asked him to play along and he smiled. Pete walked over to Chloe and Lex.<br>
<br>
“Your dad is sleeping with your ex?” He asked Lex. “Man, that’s screwed up.” Chloe bit her lip to keep herself from laughing.<br>
<br>
“I have to agree with you Mr. Ross,” Lex said seriously. “But then, Victoria and I were never an official couple per se, not like Chloe and I are, so I really have no complaints on the topic.” Pete smiled at Lex’s gall, and almost erupted in laughter when Victoria looked like she was going to blow steam out of her ears.<br>
<br>
“I’ll be sure and give your father your regards,” Victoria sneered at Lex, hoping that her statement would get a reaction out of him. This visit wasn’t going anywhere near how she had planned it.<br>
<br>
“My father is already aware of how I regard him,” Lex said dryly. Victoria clenched her hands into fists, let them go, and then she plastered a fake smile on her face.<br>
<br>
“I see,” she said. “Well both of you have a good evening then.” She ignored Pete and walked out of the Talon. Pete and Chloe both started laughing hysterically.<br>
<br>
“Damn!” Pete said. “I thought she was going to claw your eyes out for a minute there.” Chloe nodded.<br>
<br>
“Nah, her fake nails would have come off. She couldn’t risk that,” Chloe said. She turned to Lex. “You do realize she’s going to tell your dad whatever she thinks she knows about us?” Lex smirked.<br>
<br>
“I’m counting on it,” he said. ‘Damn,’ Chloe thought. She thought that would have made him concede defeat, but it hadn’t. She wondered what it would take to get him to lose. Clark and Lana braved their way over to the table.<br>
<br>
“Hi guys!” Lana greeted cheerfully. Chloe smiled at them, and then it hit her. The entire time she had been ‘playing’ with Lex, she hadn’t thought about her angst over the Clark Kent situation. Huh. ‘Interesting,’ she thought.<br>
<br>
“Hi Lana,” Chloe replied. She slid off of Lex’s lap and grabbed her bag from the floor. “And bye. I have to go now or I’m going to miss my bus.” Clark grabbed her arm.<br>
<br>
“I can give you a ride home,” he said. Lex frowned. ‘He picks now to be chivalrous?’ Lex thought. He stood up and cleared his throat, and then territorially placed his hand on the small of Chloe’s back.<br>
<br>
“I’ll take her, but thanks for your concern Clark,” Lex said. Clark eyed Lex with suspicion and then looked at Chloe.<br>
<br>
“Um, that whole thing with you sitting on his lap and kissing him, that was a game or something right? To make Victoria angry?” Clark’s questions came out uneasy and tinged with hopefulness. Chloe looked up at Lex with a smile and she could see him smirking. If he thought she was going to lose now, he had another thing coming.<br>
<br>
“Uh, well, no Clark,” Chloe said. Clark furrowed his brow and Lex looked a little surprised. Pete looked suspicious. “Lex and I are seeing each other now. You’re okay with that right?” Lana smiled broadly and let out a little giddy giggle. She gave Chloe a huge hug and pulled back.<br>
<br>
“Ooh! I knew it!” Lana proclaimed. “You guys have been doing the whole mating ritual thing for weeks now. I just knew it! I’m so happy for you Chloe!” Chloe was in shock, but she managed to smile.<br>
<br>
