<br>
“What about me?” Clark asked Lex, but was still partially looking at Pete. Lex grinned.<br>
<br>
“Under the circumstances, I don’t think that would be a very good idea,” Lex said. Clark narrowed his eyes slightly.<br>
<br>
“Why?” He asked. Lex leaned forward in his chair.<br>
<br>
“Clark, you told me that Chloe used to have feelings,” Lex winced a little but tried not to show it, “other than friendship for you.” Clark nodded. “I don’t think it would make her very comfortable to have her former crush sitting at the table with us.” Clark paled. He hadn’t thought of himself in that context. Secretly, he was still kind of hoping that Chloe liked him, but just didn’t want to ruin their friendship.<br>
<br>
“Oh,” Clark said. “I guess that makes sense.” Pete had to hand it to Lex. He had managed to make the whole thing sound like his idea, and still incorporate it into the game. Chloe would have a difficult time winning this one. Pete inwardly frowned. He had no doubt that Lex was just using the game to get Chloe’s attention, and he had a sinking feeling that it was going to work.<br>
<br>
