<br>
“Hey Lex,” she greeted. Lex turned his head to look at her. His lips spread into an appreciative smile when he took in her appearance. She was wearing a simple wine colored dress that hung to her curves without looking cheap. ‘Not that she ever could,’ he pondered.<br>
<br>
“Chloe,” he said and held his hand out for her. She didn’t bother to raise an eyebrow or motion for Lex not to be that way around her dad. Instead, she walked over and took his hand. Gabe watched the scene with confusion and a tinge of suspicion. He cleared his throat and looked at Chloe.<br>
<br>
“Something I should know about?” Gabe asked as he folded his arms across his chest. Chloe took a deep breath and smiled at her dad.<br>
<br>
“What do you mean?” She asked, feigning innocence. Gabe motioned to their joined hands with his head and Chloe briefly followed his gaze. “Oh! Lex and I are – seeing each other,” she paused when Gabe’s eyes grew large. “Sort of,” she quickly added. Lex smirked at her, but inwardly frowned. He would be happy if he won the game, but it would be a small consolation compared to what he really wanted, and for that to happen then the game would need to keep going for a while. Chloe looked up and saw his smirk. She barely narrowed her eyes at him and plastered a fake smile on her face. “You didn’t tell him?” Lex returned her look and wrapped his arm around Chloe’s back.<br>
<br>
“Don’t worry Gabe, I have nothing but honorable intentions toward your daughter,” Lex said. Chloe held back a snort. She wondered how he was able to say that with a straight face. Despite the fact that she was wearing heels, she rose to her tiptoes and kissed Lex on the cheek.<br>
<br>
“If we don’t leave now, we’re going to be late,” she murmured into his ear. Lex tried to ignore the tingle that shot down his spine when he felt her warm breath in his ear. He smiled at her and nodded once to Gabe. Lex kept his arm tightly wrapped around Chloe’s back.<br>
<br>
“Good night Gabe,” Lex said. Chloe almost started laughing when she saw the look of disbelief on her dad’s face. She smiled brightly and walked over to give him a quick hug.<br>
<br>
“I’ll be back by eleven,” she said. Lex arched an eyebrow.<br>
<br>
“You will?” He asked. She glared at him and he smiled. Chloe shook her head.<br>
<br>
“Night Dad,” she said and waved goodbye to him. Gabe stood in the doorway and watched his daughter walk with his boss, Lex Luthor, to Lex’s car, which probably cost more than he made in a year. He sighed. There were definite disadvantages to raising a strong willed daughter. Gabe mumbled something to himself about her being grounded when she got home and then he shut the door.<br>
<br>
Lex sped along Smallville’s back roads and was surprised when Chloe didn’t seem even a little bit frightened. Dangerous speeding usually got a good reaction out of most of the women he had dated. In fear, they would grip onto anything close, which would generally be him. But Chloe wasn’t fazed at all. She looked completely comfortable, leaning back in the leather seat and gazing out the window.<br>
<br>
“I know what you’re thinking,” Chloe said, breaking the silence that had encompassed them. Lex glanced at her.<br>
<br>
“Do you? I didn’t realize you had developed your Jedi abilities,” Lex quipped. Chloe burst out in laughter.<br>
<br>
“You’re a Star Wars fan?” She asked. He raised an eyebrow.<br>
<br>
“You’re the one who can read minds,” he said. “You tell me.” She chuckled.<br>
<br>
“I’m going to say yes,” she said after a moment of mock thoughtfulness. He smirked.<br>
<br>
“And I’m going to say that was just a lucky guess,” he replied. Chloe shrugged. “Now what were you going to say earlier?”<br>
<br>
“Oh,” Chloe said, snapping back to her original thoughts. “I was going to say that you were awfully quiet, so you were probably thinking that you were going to lose the game at the dinner tonight.” The confident grin on her face made Lex smile.<br>
<br>
“Actually, I was thinking how surprised I was that you didn’t lose in front of your dad,” Lex lied. Chloe’s smile faded.<br>
<br>
“Yeah, that was pretty hard,” she admitted. “I have a bad feeling that I’m going to be grounded when I get back.” Lex smiled sympathetically at her.<br>
<br>
“Sorry,” he said. She shrugged.<br>
<br>
“It was a risk,” she said. “So how well do you and your dad get along?” Lex’s face went to a stone-like appearance.<br>
<br>
“Not well,” he replied. Chloe felt bad for him. Although Lex wasn’t showing any emotional response, which in itself was an indicator of how bad he must feel about the situation. She decided to try and cheer him up.<br>
<br>
“So how far am I allowed to take this thing tonight?” She asked with a gleam in her eye. Lex felt a grin creep across his lips.<br>
<br>
“As far as you’d like,” he said suggestively. Chloe started laughing.<br>
<br>
“I don’t want your dad to get mad at you,” she said and then looked pensive. “Although, that ‘would’ probably give me the upper hand in winning the game.” It was Lex’s turn to chuckle. He pulled the car over in front of the manor.<br>
<br>
“I think I should warn you,” he said as he opened her door for her. “My father has a tendency to.” He paused and flinched ever so slightly. Chloe raised an eyebrow.<br>
<br>
“A tendency to?” She repeated. Lex grimaced.<br>
<br>
“He’s going to hit on you,” he said with a disgusted sigh. Chloe’s eyes grew wide.<br>
<br>
“You’re joking,” she said. “You’re saying this to throw me off my game, right?” Lex’s expression didn’t change and she paled. Chloe’s mouth dropped open, but she quickly shut it. “Oh.” Chloe was pulled out of her thoughts by the sound of a car horn. Both Lex and Chloe turned around to see Pete parking his car in the driveway. She furrowed her brow. “What’s Pete doing here?” She asked. Lex grinned and placed a hand on the small of her back.<br>
<br>
“I thought tonight might go easier for you if he was here,” Lex said. She gave him a look that said she clearly didn’t believe him and his grin turned into a smile. “Pete said he had to be here if he was going to be part of the game,” Lex admitted. Chloe laughed and walked over to Pete to give him a hug.<br>
<br>
