<br>
“Well, I’m glad you’re here. It just wouldn’t be a game without you,” she said. Pete smiled and Lex cleared his throat.<br>
<br>
“You’re supposed to be doting on ‘me’ Miss Sullivan,” he reminded her. Chloe and Pete exchanged an amused look and she let go of Pete’s arm. She walked over and stood on her toes to kiss his cheek.<br>
<br>
“Sorry dear,” she chimed. Lex smirked and wrapped his arms around her. Instinctively, she placed her hands on his upper arms. It caught her a little off guard since they weren’t in the house yet and Pete already knew about the game. She gave him a questioning look and he smiled down at her.<br>
<br>
“We have an audience,” he murmured as he inched his face closer to her. “Victoria is standing by the window.”<br>
<br>
“Oh,” Chloe said. Lex leaned down and placed a gentle kiss on her lips. Her hands ran up his arms and around his neck as she allowed herself to melt into it. Their mouths became more demanding, and they only broke apart when Pete cleared his throat loudly.<br>
<br>
