<br>
“As I’ll ever be,” she mumbled. “I just hope that he’s not as bad as he was the last time I met him.” Both Lex and Pete looked surprised.<br>
<br>
“You’ve met Lex’s dad before?” Pete asked. Chloe stared ahead blankly.<br>
<br>
“Yeah,” she said. Lex furrowed his brow.<br>
<br>
“Why didn’t you tell me?” Lex asked. Chloe shook her head a little to snap her out of her stupor.<br>
<br>
“Not so much an experience that I wanted to relive,” she admitted. Lex stopped walking and made eye contact with her.<br>
<br>
“Did he hurt you?” Lex asked, a menacing quality lining his voice. Chloe smiled.<br>
<br>
“Not like you think,” she said. “He basically told me that I shouldn’t waste my time with journalism and I should put my obvious attributes to better use.” She cringed when she said it. Pete shivered.<br>
<br>
“Dirty old man,” Pete commented. The expression on Lex’s face told Pete that he agreed with him.<br>
<br>
“Don’t worry Chloe. Both Pete and I are here to protect you,” Lex said. Chloe laughed and started walking again.<br>
<br>
“I’m quite capable of taking care of myself, thank you very much,” she said. Lex turned to Pete.<br>
<br>
“Is she always this stubborn?” Lex asked. Pete smiled and cocked his head.<br>
<br>
“Don’t ask me,” Pete replied and slapped Lex on the back as he started walking again. “She’s your pretend girlfriend.” When they arrived at the dining room, they found Lionel and Victoria already waiting for them.<br>
<br>
“Lex,” she said happily and strolled over to him. She gave a death glare to Chloe, who in return just smiled. Victoria raised an eyebrow at Pete’s presence. “I thought just you and…” She looked at Chloe as if she had forgotten her name.<br>
<br>
“Chloe,” Lex filled in for her.<br>
<br>
“Chloe,” Victoria repeated with disgust. “I thought only the two of you were to be joining us for dinner tonight.” Lex motioned toward Pete.<br>
<br>
“I’m sorry to hear that your information was yet again so unreliable,” Lex smirked. “Pete Ross, Victoria Hardwick,” he introduced. Victoria huffed and made no motion to even acknowledge the introduction. Instead, she walked over to where Lionel now stood. Lionel tapped with his cane until he reached his son.<br>
<br>
“I am to imply from this fascinating conversation that the lovely Miss Sullivan is now in our presence?” Lionel sneered. Chloe rolled her eyes at Lex and Pete almost started laughing.<br>
<br>
“Mr. Luthor,” Chloe greeted in as pleasant of a voice as she could come up with. She clung onto Lex’s arm as if it was for dear life.<br>
<br>
“Now, now dear. Call me Lionel,” he said. Chloe glared at him. ‘Too bad he can’t see all the bad looks I’m giving him,’ she thought.<br>
<br>
“I’d rather not,” she admitted in an almost cold voice. Lionel’s eyebrows raised in surprise at her courage to speak to him like that. He smirked.<br>
<br>
“Apparently you’ve never heard the phrase ‘you can attract more flies with honey’,” Lionel responded. Chloe smiled broadly.<br>
<br>
“Actually I have Mr. Luthor,” she said. “I just have no desire to attract flies.” Lex and Pete both snickered. Lex rubbed his hand on Chloe’s back and spoke into her ear.<br>
<br>
“Shall we?” Lex asked, guiding her to the table. He had a feeling that tonight would be the turning point in the game and he couldn’t wait.<br>
