<br>
“Are you alright?” He asked in a concerned voice. “You’ve barely touched your meal.” Chloe grinned.<br>
<br>
“I’m fine,” she said. “Just not very hungry.” So far, the dinner had been okay, but Lionel and Victoria were starting to get to her. She didn’t care about Victoria so much, just because she wasn’t really going out with Lex, but Lionel had been relentlessly making sexual innuendos toward her and she was ready to slug him. Chloe decided to up the ante for the game. She tilted her head at Lex. “At least not for this,” she said in a suggestive voice. Lex nearly spit out the water he was sipping. When he returned to his normal breathing state he smirked at her and ran his hand further up her leg. He nuzzled his face into her hair.<br>
<br>
“Say the word and we can leave,” he murmured. Chloe smiled and Pete rolled his eyes.<br>
Pete had been pushing the food into his mouth like there was no tomorrow, and wasn’t thrilled with the possibility of leaving the wonderful meal behind.<br>
<br>
“Would you two knock it off?” Pete asked. “Nobody here wants to see you doing all that mushy stuff.” Lionel grinned.<br>
<br>
“Quite astute of you Mr. Ross,” Lionel agreed. Lex ignored them and began to kiss Chloe. She let out a small moan as he slid his tongue into her mouth. Victoria fumed and crossed her arms. This little blonde girl was taking the attention that should have been hers. Not just from Lex, but from Lionel too. ‘Luckily I still have one card left up my sleeve,’ she thought.<br>
<br>
“So when is the wedding?” Victoria asked. Lionel started choking slightly as his wine went down the wrong way. Pete smiled. This was the opening he had been waiting for. Finally, he could get back at them for making romantic gestures toward each other all night, without making it look like he wasn’t playing along with the game.<br>
<br>
“Yeah,” Pete started to get his evil grin on his face. “Have you guys set a date yet?” Lex and Chloe pulled away from each other and shared a look. It was a look of determination, silently asking how far the other person how far they were willing to go with the game in order to win. Chloe smirked and turned to the other people at the table. She was going to win this no matter what.<br>
<br>
“We haven’t talked about getting married,” she said in a sweet voice. “Right now, we’re just enjoying each other’s company.” She cast a challenging glance at Lex and he grinned.<br>
<br>
“You don’t want to get married?” He asked, trying to put an inflection of surprise and hurt into his question. He leaned closer and nipped at her neck. She tried to control the sensation that she suddenly felt coursing through her body, but was unsuccessful.<br>
<br>
“I, I,” she stammered when she felt his tongue on the shell of her ear. “I hadn’t really considered it.&quot;<br>
<br>
“Alexander, that’s quite enough,” Lionel said. “Thank God I only have to hear you doing unspeakable things to the girl.” Lex smirked.<br>
<br>
“I could be doing more if you hadn’t forced us to come to dinner tonight,” Lex replied in a calm voice. Chloe and Pete both had to bite back their laughter when they saw the looks on Lionel and Victoria’s faces. Lionel pulled back his expression and put on his game face.<br>
<br>
“I didn’t force ‘you’ to come son,” Lionel said. “I merely extended an invitation to the lovely young woman next to you.”<br>
<br>
“And she’s turned you down repeatedly through the evening,” Lex observed and sat back in his chair. Lionel sloughed off the comment.<br>
<br>
“Perhaps she’s not aware of the fact that I’m considerably more solvent than you are,” Lionel sneered. “Young lady, if you’re going to date someone for his money, you should at least do it right.” It was an insult and a pick up line at the same time. Chloe shook her head in disbelief.<br>
<br>
“I’m not dating Lex for his money,” Chloe responded. ‘I’m not dating him at all,’ she thought. Lionel seemed surprised, but barely let it show.<br>
<br>
“Of course you are my dear,” he said. “You may not realize it, but you are. What other possible attraction could there be? You were attracted to his power, his position, the way he exudes strength. All of those things come with having money.” Chloe took a deep breath and turned to Lex.<br>
<br>
“If I hit him will you be mad at me?” She asked through gritted teeth. Lex chuckled.<br>
<br>
“Actually, I’d love to see that,” he answered. Pete smiled and nodded.<br>
<br>
“Me too,” Pete said. Chloe smiled and shook her head, and then she looked at Lex.<br>
<br>
“Maybe we should just leave,” she said. Lex grinned and pushed his chair away from the table. He stood up and extended his hand to help Chloe out of her seat.<br>
<br>
“Don’t be so hasty,” Lionel said. “I promise to behave myself if Chloe can give me a valid reason, other than your money, as to why she likes you.” He paused for a second and Chloe shivered at the pure evil she saw in his expression. “In fact, I’ll even give your relationship with her my blessing.” Lex glanced at Chloe and then back to his father.<br>
<br>
“I don’t care if we have your blessing or not,” Lex replied. Chloe slipped her hand into his and gave it a small squeeze.<br>
<br>
“It’s okay,” she told Lex. Chloe walked over to Lionel. “You want to know why I like your son?” He nodded. “He’s cute, he’s smart, he’s funny, and,” she paused when a deliciously evil thought crept into her head. “He’s great in bed.” Pete burst out in laughter, but turned it into an uncomfortable cough when everyone looked at him. Lionel reached out for Chloe and found her hand, but she quickly ripped it away from him.<br>
<br>
“Darling, if you think Alexander is a good lover, it just proves that you’re ready for someone more…experienced,” Lionel said in a sensual tone. Even Victoria cringed. This evening hadn’t gone the way she wanted at all. Chloe laughed.<br>
<br>
“Not interested,” she said. “And I thought you said you were going to behave yourself?” Lionel smiled and Lex frowned. Was Chloe flirting with him? Lex walked over to her and wrapped his arm around her waist. He leaned down and sweetly kissed the crook of her neck.<br>
<br>
“I thought we were leaving,” Lex half whispered. She tilted her head to look at him.<br>
<br>
“Absolutely,” she agreed. Pete got up from his seat and walked to the dining room door. He casually leaned against the frame while waiting for Chloe and Lex to say their goodbyes.<br>
<br>
“Father,” Lex acknowledged as a farewell greeting. Lionel smirked.<br>
<br>
“Son,” he responded. Lex and Chloe started to walk away. “Chloe?” She turned around.<br>
<br>
“It was a pleasure dining with you. I do hope I didn’t make you uncomfortable,” Lionel said polite, charming tone. Lex squared his jaw and clenched his hands into fists, but quickly released them when Chloe wrapped her arm around him as well. He stared down at her with a questioning expression on his face.<br>
<br>
“The only way you would have made me uncomfortable is if I would have taken you up on your offers,” Chloe said to Lionel. “Now, if you’ll excuse us, Lex and I would like to spend some time alone this evening.” Lex smirked and walked out the door with Chloe and Pete. Lionel turned his head in Victoria’s general direction.<br>
<br>
“He was smirking wasn’t he?” He asked. Victoria sighed and came to sit down next to him.<br>
<br>
“Yes,” she confirmed. Lionel nodded.<br>
<br>
“I hate that smirk.”<br>
<br>
~*~*~*~*~*~<br>
<br>
“You think I’m cute?” Lex asked, reminding Chloe of what she told his father. Lex had a goofy smile on his face and Chloe rolled her eyes.<br>
<br>
“Sure,” she answered. His smiled grew more confident.<br>
<br>
“And smart? And funny?” He continued.<br>
<br>
“Are you done?” She asked impatiently. Chloe refused to make eye contact with him. They were only five minutes into the drive back to her house and he couldn’t stop talking about how she had handled Lionel.<br>
<br>
“No,” he said. Chloe smiled.<br>
<br>
“I also said you were good in bed, although I have no evidence to back up that claim,” she said. ‘That should shut him up,’ she thought. Lex smirked.<br>
<br>
“I believe you said ‘great’, not ‘good’, and I’d be more than happy to show you,” he responded. Her eyes grew a little wider, but then she started laughing. Chloe playfully hit his arm.<br>
<br>
“You almost had me going there for a minute,” she said. Lex grinned.<br>
<br>
“Did I?” His voice was smooth and husky, and Chloe looked away from him so he wouldn’t see her blush. “Tell me Chloe, is our game working?” She looked back at him in confusion.<br>
<br>
“What do you mean?” She asked. He grinned at her response.<br>
<br>
“When was the last time you thought about Clark?” Lex asked. Chloe seemed surprised, although more by her answer than by his question.<br>
<br>
“A couple days now,” she admitted. Lex nodded.<br>
<br>
“That was the point of the game wasn’t it?” He asked. Chloe smiled in agreement.<br>
<br>
“Yeah,” she said. He pulled up to her house and stopped the car. Lex briefly glanced at the clock on the dashboard.<br>
<br>
“I got you home early,” he observed. “I don’t suppose that’s going to cut you any slack as far as a possible grounding is concerned?” Chloe shook her head and Lex got out of the car to open the door without waiting for the rest of her response.<br>
<br>
“Probably not,” she said when he gave her his hand to help her out. He grinned down at her and placed his hands on her hips.<br>
<br>
“Well, in that case,” he said. Lex moved his lips toward hers and they gently touched. Chloe was beginning to see that their game had definite advantages. She liked the way he kissed, the way he felt. Chloe pushed the thoughts out of her head as she pulled him closer and deepened the kiss. ‘I will not like Lex Luthor,’ she told herself. Their tongues slid together and she moaned. ‘I will not like…oh, what the hell.’ They continued their passionate embrace until Chloe needed to breathe. She rested her forehead on his chest.<br>
<br>
“Was my dad watching?” She asked in a hushed voice. Lex furrowed his brow.<br>
<br>
“I don’t know,” he admitted. “Why?” Chloe raised her eyes to look at him.<br>
<br>
“Isn’t that why you kissed me?” She asked in surprise. He smiled and noticed that she hadn’t pushed herself out of his arms.<br>
<br>
“Chloe, do you really think I chose myself for the game by chance?” Lex asked. She narrowed her eyes at him.<br>
<br>
“I knew you liked playing Lana zone with me, I just figured that,” she said, her words cut off by him kissing her again.<br>
<br>
“If you hadn’t noticed, you’ve had my full attention for some time now,” Lex started to explain. “I just wanted to make sure I had yours.” Chloe’s mouth dropped open a little, but she turned it into a smile. She brought his mouth down to hers once again and kissed him.<br>
<br>
“You do.”<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
The End<br>
